[1] Cholera - Zambia (Kitwe)
Date: Sun 7 Jan 2018
Source: Zambia Reports [edited]
https://zambiareports.com/2018/01/07/kitwe-records-first-two-cases-cholera/


Kitwe District has recorded its 1st 2 cases of cholera involving children below the age of 2. Despite the early preparations by Kitwe mayor Christopher Kang'ombe and district commissioner Binwell Mpundu, the epidemic has hit the mining town breaking out from 2 rural compounds, Zambia and Buchi. Binwell Mpundu said the 2 cases of cholera are being treated at Kitwe Teaching Hospital.

"I wish to confirm that here in Kitwe, we have recorded so far 2 cases of cholera, very little children that have tested positive for cholera. There is need for the public to take precaution now that we are also affected," Mpundu stated. He added that with the cases of cholera now recorded in the district, the sale of any edible foods on the market has since been banned until such a time the situation will normalise.

Mpundu has, however, advised the public not to panic, as the 2 cases recorded are being treated and measures have been put in place to avoid further outbreaks. "However, I wish to inform the public not to panic as the 2 victims who are children are being attended to by health personnel, but there is need to take precautions to avoid further outbreaks," said Mpundu.

[byline: Andre Musonda]

